-- India's ITC, hopes of global stimulus lift NSE index to record high
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 05:09AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Dec 4 (Reuters) - India's NSE index hit a record high on Thursday on continued hopes for global monetary stimulus measures, while ITC Ltd <ITC.NS> surged more than 5 percent to a six-month high on media reports the government was rethinking a potential ban on the sale of loose cigarettes.

ITC provisionally soared 5.5 percent after earlier marking its highest intraday level since May, while Hindustan Unilever <HLL.NS> ended higher 0.7 percent.